name: BLACKPINK
data: Blackpink is a South Korean girl group formed by YG Entertainment, consisting of members Jisoo, Jennie, Ros√©, and Lisa. The group debuted in August 2016 with their single album Square One, which featured "Whistle" and "Boombayah", their first number-one entries on South Korea's Gaon Digital Chart and the Billboard World Digital track Sales chart, respectively.
